WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:07.000
Downloaded from
YTS.MX

00:08.000 --> 00:13.000
Official YIFY movies site:
YTS.MX

00:51.668 --> 00:57.436
"REFLECTIONS OF A BLENDER"

01:32.175 --> 01:36.373
I can't stay silent
like I used to.

01:36.713 --> 01:39.614
Damned fever that keeps
me away from the fridge...

01:39.816 --> 01:44.219
the stove,
the sink, the clock...

01:44.454 --> 01:47.389
from all these objects
that work machine-like...

01:47.591 --> 01:49.650
as men like to say.

01:49.860 --> 01:51.885
And don't care
or even know that...

01:52.095 --> 01:57.158
they are called objects,
stuff, kitchen appliances.

02:04.708 --> 02:07.973
And what about me?
Appliance and what else?

02:08.178 --> 02:09.304
Still blades...

02:09.513 --> 02:12.573
but inside me,
a flow of ideas, thoughts...

02:12.783 --> 02:16.241
sensations, grinding
and tearing at my silence...

02:16.453 --> 02:20.184
spinning and crushing
like sharp edges.

02:20.557 --> 02:23.321
Blender and witness...

02:23.527 --> 02:26.360
grinding machine
and accomplice...

02:26.563 --> 02:28.463
to all the events that
altered the life...

02:28.665 --> 02:30.155
of the owners of this house...

02:30.367 --> 02:32.858
and my condition as object.

02:51.421 --> 02:54.515
- I'm leaving.
- Good luck.

02:54.858 --> 02:58.589
- God's will be done.
- Amen.

03:11.541 --> 03:14.840
My husband's been
missing eight days.

03:15.045 --> 03:16.637
He left one morning
to go to the market...

03:16.847 --> 03:18.872
and never came back.

03:19.082 --> 03:20.777
Does your husband
have any mental problems?

03:20.984 --> 03:24.010
No, sir.
Onofre is a normal man...

03:24.221 --> 03:26.553
healthy, hardworking.

03:26.756 --> 03:29.748
He's never been gone
for so long.

03:31.228 --> 03:34.755
- How old is your husband?
- 67.

03:34.965 --> 03:37.798
- Any children?
- No, sir.

03:39.202 --> 03:40.567
Has he had any disagreements...

03:40.770 --> 03:43.432
with anyone
in the past few days?

03:43.640 --> 03:45.471
No, thank God.

03:45.675 --> 03:47.973
The whole neighborhood
was fond of him...

03:48.178 --> 03:50.442
He was respected at work.

03:50.947 --> 03:54.542
Everyone's worried about
his disappearance.

03:56.319 --> 03:59.288
- Ms...
- Elvira.

03:59.523 --> 04:04.859
Ms. Elvira. Have you considered
the possibility that he has left?

04:05.929 --> 04:07.954
Left how?

04:08.331 --> 04:11.528
You mean to say
that he abandoned me?

04:11.735 --> 04:14.431
Unfortunately, it is not
altogether impossible.

04:14.638 --> 04:16.435
I have seen a number
of such cases.

04:16.640 --> 04:21.407
Lieutenant, we've been
married for over 40 years.

04:21.611 --> 04:24.079
Lots of harmony and
tenderness between us.

04:24.281 --> 04:26.511
Why would Onofre leave me?

04:26.716 --> 04:28.274
Another woman, for instance.

04:28.485 --> 04:31.943
No! The police
can't even think that.

04:32.756 --> 04:34.587
Onofre is a faithful husband.

04:34.791 --> 04:38.625
He's not that kind of man,
thank God!

04:39.429 --> 04:44.264
Well, Ms. Elvira,
I'll file a report...

04:44.467 --> 04:47.630
and assign a detective
to the case.

04:47.837 --> 04:50.567
But I can tell you this:

04:50.774 --> 04:53.265
the first suspect
on his disappearance...

04:53.476 --> 04:55.740
is you.

05:01.184 --> 05:03.311
I wonder what happened.

05:03.520 --> 05:05.078
The hand on the clock has
turned a few times...

05:05.288 --> 05:07.950
and she hasn't come back yet.

05:10.160 --> 05:12.151
Maybe she
can deceive the police...

05:12.362 --> 05:14.728
and calm herself down.

05:27.177 --> 05:30.908
What happened?

05:31.314 --> 05:33.214
The worst.

05:33.416 --> 05:35.316
Did you go to the station?

05:35.518 --> 05:37.247
Yes.

05:37.988 --> 05:39.387
They suspected me.

05:39.990 --> 05:42.424
How come?

05:42.792 --> 05:44.521
Fuinha!

05:50.233 --> 05:52.827
I didn't like that
Fuinha character.

05:53.036 --> 05:56.528
- Why not?
- I didn't like his nose.

05:56.740 --> 06:00.369
He looks like a snoop.
With a thin nose.

06:00.577 --> 06:02.477
Dangerous.

06:02.679 --> 06:05.079
Once I left,
he followed me around.

06:05.282 --> 06:08.012
Is it normal to follow
a person right away...

06:08.218 --> 06:10.083
Who knows...

06:10.687 --> 06:14.521
or did he suspect
me from beginning?

06:15.292 --> 06:17.226
Where did you go?

06:17.427 --> 06:19.861
First I went to the church.

06:20.330 --> 06:24.027
Didn't you say you couldn't
face the image of Christ?

06:24.234 --> 06:26.134
I prayed with closed eyes.

06:26.336 --> 06:31.137
But I thought God could
see inside people.

06:31.574 --> 06:32.939
Shut up.

06:33.143 --> 06:36.135
What do you know
about religion? Shut up.

06:36.379 --> 06:39.007
We all pray any way we can.

06:39.749 --> 06:43.947
And then I went shopping
for these fruit.

06:44.154 --> 06:46.645
You made thing
too easy for him.

06:46.890 --> 06:48.619
You could buy fruit
some other day!

06:51.061 --> 06:52.494
Why didn't you come
straight home?

06:52.696 --> 06:54.789
Enough talking,
you're too nosy.

06:54.998 --> 06:56.260
Get to work!

06:57.233 --> 06:58.666
What are you doing?

06:58.868 --> 07:00.802
It's been days since I've had an
avocado shake.

07:01.004 --> 07:02.062
Elvira.

07:02.272 --> 07:03.603
I don't feel like
blending now.

07:03.807 --> 07:04.796
Why not?

07:05.008 --> 07:07.033
I don't feel well.

07:07.243 --> 07:09.609
Leave the avocado
for some other time.

07:13.616 --> 07:15.607
They might see your blade.

07:15.819 --> 07:18.879
You look like a weapon,
not a blender.

07:19.089 --> 07:21.580
You're the one who
made a weapon of me.

07:21.791 --> 07:23.088
And now, they'll blame me.

07:23.293 --> 07:25.853
Don't be afraid.
Just help me.

07:26.062 --> 07:30.829
- Haven't I done all I can?
- Yes, but I need a bit more.

07:33.169 --> 07:35.137
- And then, Elvira?
- Then what?

07:35.338 --> 07:38.830
When it's over,
what will you do with me?

07:39.042 --> 07:43.672
Nothing; you'll go on
working as a blender.

07:44.547 --> 07:46.879
I don't want you to break me.

07:47.083 --> 07:49.347
I won't break you, silly!

07:49.552 --> 07:51.679
Nutty blender!

07:52.489 --> 07:54.480
Let's grind!

07:56.393 --> 07:58.918
Get to work!
Quit snarling.

08:00.797 --> 08:02.162
Bastard!

08:02.365 --> 08:04.959
You're no good anymore.
Too noisy.

08:05.168 --> 08:09.935
Watch it, you, bastard.

08:12.442 --> 08:15.206
Ok. Now you're singing,
aren't you?

08:18.281 --> 08:23.378
That's it. I like that.
Sing my little bird.

08:23.586 --> 08:26.146
Why can't you always
work like this?

08:26.356 --> 08:27.823
Bastard.

08:28.024 --> 08:29.787
You sing when you want to...

08:29.993 --> 08:32.757
and when you don't,
you snarl!

08:32.962 --> 08:36.420
And when you're up to it,
you can grind perfectly.

08:36.633 --> 08:40.763
That I do well;
shakes are my specialty.

08:40.970 --> 08:44.667
You've gotta grind whatever
I put in there, got it?

08:44.874 --> 08:47.707
I did, Elvira.
I ground what you asked me.

08:47.911 --> 08:51.870
But you neighed like a horse.
The neighbors must have heard you.

08:52.081 --> 08:55.949
- It wasn't easy, Elvira.
- Stop yelling.

08:56.152 --> 09:00.612
Then stop pointing fingers.
I did my best.

09:00.824 --> 09:04.282
I'll die repeating that.
I did my best.

09:05.595 --> 09:08.086
You find it disgusting?

09:08.698 --> 09:12.099
Doesn't the shake look tasty?

09:17.006 --> 09:21.102
Your stomach's been
empty for too long.

09:21.778 --> 09:24.838
Go on. Drink a little.

09:26.282 --> 09:30.150
Elvira. Take a sip.
Go on.

09:31.955 --> 09:37.222
That's it.
Drink up.

09:37.427 --> 09:38.416
What's the matter?

09:51.808 --> 09:55.676
What's this taste
you put in the shake?

09:55.879 --> 09:58.780
I put the taste you gave me.

09:59.716 --> 10:01.616
I put in avocado,
milk and sugar.

10:01.818 --> 10:04.150
You gave me something rotten.

10:04.354 --> 10:07.915
You taste that in everything.

10:08.124 --> 10:09.614
The water doesn't
taste like this.

10:09.826 --> 10:12.420
Yesterday you said the banana
and the orange had it.

10:12.629 --> 10:14.187
And the bread, too.

10:14.397 --> 10:17.332
So, it's not me, you're the
one tasting it everywhere.

10:17.534 --> 10:21.595
Don't you try to trick me,
when you least expect it, I'll...

10:21.804 --> 10:24.068
- What?
- Watch it.

10:24.707 --> 10:25.696
It's Fuinha!

10:25.909 --> 10:28.104
Don't panic.
It may be a neighbor.

10:28.311 --> 10:29.471
I'll throw it away.

10:29.679 --> 10:32.045
No, Elvira, don't do that.

10:32.248 --> 10:33.272
What about the taste of death?

10:33.483 --> 10:35.610
There's no such taste.

10:35.818 --> 10:37.080
What if it's Fuinha?

10:37.287 --> 10:41.155
Elvira, the house is clean
and you're alone. Go on!

10:41.357 --> 10:43.757
- Elvira!
- May Jesus be with me.

10:43.960 --> 10:45.154
- Amen.
- I'm coming.

10:45.361 --> 10:47.761
Go, Elvira. Go!

10:53.036 --> 10:55.266
Hi, Ms. Elvira.

10:55.505 --> 10:56.972
Long time no see.

10:57.340 --> 10:58.466
Has the old man come back?

10:58.675 --> 10:59.664
Nothing so far.

10:59.876 --> 11:01.400
- I have news.
- A letter?

11:01.611 --> 11:03.010
No. May I come in?

11:03.212 --> 11:04.839
It won't take long.

11:05.048 --> 11:07.414
I need to tell you something.

11:10.520 --> 11:12.886
Oh, I miss Mr. Onofre.

11:14.257 --> 11:16.919
So, you fixed the blender?

11:17.126 --> 11:19.993
Avocado, yum!

11:20.196 --> 11:23.256
I don't know it's ok,
the avocado might be spoiled.

11:23.466 --> 11:27.994
Let's have a taste of it,
so we know for sure.

11:28.471 --> 11:31.531
Your shakes are delicious.

11:32.342 --> 11:38.281
You mind if I sit?
I've been walking.

11:38.481 --> 11:43.612
Drink it slowly,
it's the only glass.

11:48.091 --> 11:51.185
The best shake in town.

11:54.464 --> 11:55.863
What do you have
to tell me?

11:56.065 --> 12:01.230
I don't mean to snoop into
other people's lives...

12:01.437 --> 12:04.099
Mr. Onofre was such
a good man, wasn't he?

12:04.307 --> 12:06.867
Despite his favorite
soccer team.

12:07.076 --> 12:08.543
Cut to the chase.

12:08.745 --> 12:14.081
I'd rather deliver one thousand
letters than tell you this.

12:14.283 --> 12:15.944
Do you really have
something to say?

12:16.152 --> 12:17.642
I do.

12:19.856 --> 12:22.586
Mr. Onofre...

12:22.792 --> 12:25.955
He has... or had...

12:26.262 --> 12:27.422
an affair.

12:28.031 --> 12:31.194
- What?
- An affair.

12:31.467 --> 12:35.836
Another woman, you understand?
I saw it.

12:36.039 --> 12:38.530
What did you see?
What other woman?

12:38.741 --> 12:40.504
It's not like me to meddle
in people's lives.

12:40.710 --> 12:42.735
I was passing by the
hospital and saw him.

12:42.945 --> 12:44.173
That's a lie.

12:44.847 --> 12:46.781
Onofre wasn't that kind of man!

12:47.150 --> 12:50.449
I saw how anguished you were
and decided to tell you.

12:50.653 --> 12:53.918
She's a nurse...

12:54.123 --> 12:55.750
I shouldn't even have said that...

12:56.259 --> 12:58.352
So I talked to her...

12:58.561 --> 13:02.759
and she hadn't heard
from him in two weeks.

13:02.965 --> 13:05.263
So I decided to come here...

13:05.468 --> 13:09.131
the old man has vanished,
he's really gone.

13:09.672 --> 13:12.368
- Get out!
- I only wanted to help.

13:12.575 --> 13:14.008
I'll file a complaint
at the postal company!

13:14.210 --> 13:17.145
Go to the police
before it's too late!

13:21.084 --> 13:22.711
What the heck?!

13:22.919 --> 13:25.251
It's not like him
to nose around.

13:25.455 --> 13:27.787
But he knew who she was,
her job, her workplace.

13:27.990 --> 13:29.924
How terrible!

13:31.794 --> 13:34.194
Even the mailman knew it.

13:34.831 --> 13:38.232
How can a man
be so disrespectful?

13:41.337 --> 13:43.498
What about me?

13:44.674 --> 13:47.438
How about me all this time?

13:48.177 --> 13:50.270
Disgrace.

14:10.133 --> 14:13.398
Stop that.
Stop it!

14:14.003 --> 14:17.632
In this house things work
the way they like!

14:17.840 --> 14:18.829
You want to drip?

14:19.041 --> 14:20.133
So drip.

14:20.343 --> 14:23.141
Let water out the pipe.

14:25.481 --> 14:27.506
That's it.

14:27.717 --> 14:31.209
Flood it, flood it all.

14:32.522 --> 14:35.514
Premium eggs on sale.

14:35.725 --> 14:39.217
Potatoes. Onions. Garlic.

14:39.428 --> 14:44.331
Oranges. Lime. Quayle eggs.

14:44.634 --> 14:48.934
Bananas. Tomatoes.
Sweet Potatoes.

14:49.172 --> 14:51.868
Assorted sweets.

15:05.621 --> 15:07.350
Things have changed
in the past few days.

15:07.557 --> 15:10.583
It's unusually
tense around here.

15:10.793 --> 15:12.693
I'm never at ease
when she's awake.

15:12.895 --> 15:16.763
And even when she sleeps
my thoughts don't rest.

15:16.966 --> 15:20.959
Why did they do this to me?
What makes my engine...

15:21.170 --> 15:24.333
understand human feelings?

15:24.540 --> 15:27.907
Particularly of the people
in this house?

15:30.646 --> 15:32.705
I must have been
happy before...

15:32.915 --> 15:34.712
because I can't
remember how it was.

15:34.917 --> 15:41.481
Engines have no memory.
Nor do they need it...

15:42.825 --> 15:46.124
is already a form of happiness.

15:59.775 --> 16:03.643
Blenders are born in factories
and die in junkyards.

16:03.846 --> 16:07.077
It's a simple story,
a straight line.

16:07.283 --> 16:11.982
We're useful as long as we work.
Replaced when we break down.

16:21.030 --> 16:22.759
It's not the same
for men, though.

16:22.965 --> 16:25.729
From what I've seen,
they don't know...

16:25.935 --> 16:28.335
where they come from,
where they're going...

16:28.537 --> 16:32.564
why they're born,
why they live or die.

16:32.775 --> 16:37.508
This life full of doubt
they call "conscious life".

16:37.947 --> 16:40.381
And it's that same consciousness
they gave me...

16:40.583 --> 16:43.882
when they replaced some
parts of my mechanism.

16:51.494 --> 16:53.689
I don't know if it all
happened slowly...

16:53.896 --> 16:59.334
or suddenly,
by simply changing a screw.

16:59.535 --> 17:01.002
I don't know.

17:01.203 --> 17:06.607
I doubt my first moments
as much as any human.

17:13.749 --> 17:17.708
Assembly line,
mass production...

17:17.920 --> 17:20.855
everything seems
to start there.

17:21.123 --> 17:23.591
And if that's the start
of an object...

17:23.793 --> 17:27.889
why can't it be
the start of people too?

17:29.799 --> 17:31.892
One of the first
events I remember...

17:32.101 --> 17:34.865
it happened when I was still
a regular blender...

17:35.071 --> 17:37.562
a mere appliance.

17:39.075 --> 17:42.374
What the hell?
A piece of iron in the shake.

17:43.312 --> 17:45.041
- Iron?
- A blade.

17:45.247 --> 17:47.147
What if I'd swallowed it?

17:47.350 --> 17:49.910
It's a piece of the blender.

17:50.119 --> 17:54.715
Watch out! You might send
someone six feet under!

17:56.292 --> 17:58.192
I was placed in a corner.

17:58.461 --> 18:03.455
It was the first time
I heard perfectly well...

18:03.666 --> 18:05.497
- what people were saying.
- I made a choice...

18:05.701 --> 18:07.862
that I'd represent Cain.

18:08.070 --> 18:09.594
Before the Creator?

18:09.805 --> 18:12.672
Before the Creator
and before his creatures.

18:14.043 --> 18:16.603
The word is our key instrument.

18:16.812 --> 18:19.781
I was there all afternoon.

18:19.982 --> 18:23.748
The sound of the human voice
entranced me.

18:26.288 --> 18:31.521
I observed people and
their conversations.

19:05.594 --> 19:09.155
But everything cleared up
both inside and outside me...

19:09.365 --> 19:11.890
when they put
in the new blade.

19:12.101 --> 19:13.432
It looks like a scorpion.

19:13.636 --> 19:14.967
Looks like a weapon.

19:15.171 --> 19:17.799
Ugly beast.

19:18.908 --> 19:21.069
Back to the counter.

19:23.112 --> 19:25.376
This one will have last
'til the end, right?

19:25.915 --> 19:27.883
Another five months?

19:28.084 --> 19:29.984
Seven, Onofre, seven.

19:31.087 --> 19:33.146
What'll happen to us?

19:33.355 --> 19:35.585
Same as always.

19:35.791 --> 19:38.817
If anyone asked me,
I'd say the change of blades...

19:39.028 --> 19:42.862
made me the happiest
appliance in the world.

19:43.065 --> 19:47.263
I felt strong and sturdy
as never before.

19:47.470 --> 19:51.167
Went back to work
with renewed enthusiasm.

19:51.373 --> 19:53.841
It was like coming
out of the factory.

19:54.043 --> 19:57.570
Those were the best
seven months of my life!

19:57.780 --> 20:00.544
But they went by much,
much too quickly.

20:32.581 --> 20:37.177
The china, the coffeemaker
and other appliances were boxed.

20:38.287 --> 20:43.725
I was placed in a spot
that at first seemed uncomfortable.

20:44.126 --> 20:50.065
But I soon realized that I couldn't
wish for a better seat.

21:10.853 --> 21:14.516
I marveled at
the busy streets.

21:14.723 --> 21:18.420
That world was
stunning to me.

21:18.627 --> 21:21.721
Created by mighty beings.

21:24.066 --> 21:26.967
I looked at people's faces
on the sidewalk...

21:27.169 --> 21:32.232
crossing the streets,
driving their fantastic cars...

21:32.441 --> 21:37.105
and I felt chosen by the gods for
an unforgettable adventure.

21:39.448 --> 21:42.781
And then... I saw the fountain.

21:46.822 --> 21:50.849
The water was rising as if
trying to reach the sun.

22:26.996 --> 22:31.194
Premium eggs on sale.

22:31.800 --> 22:34.792
Directly from the farm...

22:35.638 --> 22:38.869
- How's everything?
- Fine.

22:39.074 --> 22:41.542
- Have anything for me today?
- Sadly, nothing.

22:41.744 --> 22:45.145
- Forgot all about me.
- We'd never forget you.

22:45.347 --> 22:47.440
- What did you want with him?
- A letter.

22:47.650 --> 22:49.117
You flirt with everyone,
don't you?

22:49.318 --> 22:50.910
Come on, baby.

22:51.120 --> 22:53.350
- Bye.
- Go to work now. Bye.

22:59.528 --> 23:00.756
How are you, boss?

23:00.963 --> 23:03.022
I don't boss, I beg.
Any news?

23:03.232 --> 23:08.670
Nothing yet. If I hear about a job,
I'll let you know.

23:16.845 --> 23:19.245
- Any news for me?
- Nothing yet, Mr. Onofre.

23:19.448 --> 23:21.746
No problem. Thank you.

23:46.875 --> 23:49.070
At first I missed
the smoothie shop.

23:49.278 --> 23:51.872
I enjoyed the variety
of customers...

23:52.081 --> 23:56.541
new faces, different topics,
other voices.

23:56.752 --> 23:59.619
Now it was just me
and the housewife.

23:59.822 --> 24:01.289
And sometimes
the next-door neighbor...

24:01.490 --> 24:03.788
who always chose
the same subject.

24:04.593 --> 24:07.357
- You like the manioc?
- It's great.

24:07.830 --> 24:11.095
The fresher, the tastier.

24:13.035 --> 24:17.472
I saw on TV that eating entire
grapes is good for you.

24:17.673 --> 24:18.970
Is it?

24:20.042 --> 24:23.478
- And makes you want it.
- Want what?

24:24.480 --> 24:28.280
It, Ms. Elvira.

24:31.553 --> 24:34.852
Not working?
It's a bad plug.

24:35.057 --> 24:39.323
Bad blender.
Has a mind of its own.

24:39.528 --> 24:41.587
Jeez!

24:42.731 --> 24:45.325
I like to tear the pulp
of fruit and vegetables...

24:45.534 --> 24:48.662
and stick my blade
into words and ideas.

24:49.838 --> 24:53.535
Everything turns when they
switch me on and speed me up.

24:53.742 --> 24:56.802
I work in 3 speeds:
1,2 and 3.

24:57.012 --> 25:00.038
I know people who hate
numbers and don't get math.

25:00.249 --> 25:02.342
Not me. I get it very well.

25:02.551 --> 25:06.351
Grindingly well.
1,2,3.

25:08.157 --> 25:12.355
Grinding is thinking.
Thinking is grinding.

25:22.471 --> 25:25.269
I sold the cooler,
the coffeemaker...

25:25.474 --> 25:27.408
and the small blender.

25:27.609 --> 25:30.077
Onofre, did you have to?

25:30.279 --> 25:33.442
Don't you think?
Four months and not a penny.

25:33.649 --> 25:36.641
What about us?

25:36.852 --> 25:38.547
How are we going to live?

25:38.754 --> 25:42.121
Empty stomach,
no water, no light?

25:42.324 --> 25:45.555
Why didn't you sell this blender?
It is a piece of junk.

25:45.761 --> 25:47.991
I wanted to leave
you the best.

25:48.197 --> 25:50.995
It used to be the best.
It's been rubbish for a while.

26:24.700 --> 26:27.567
Didn't tell you this old thing's crazy?

26:54.563 --> 26:57.293
I didn't see you get up today.

26:57.499 --> 27:00.468
Lots of housework to do.

27:08.043 --> 27:09.772
Help me!

27:09.978 --> 27:12.640
My leg hurts!

27:24.860 --> 27:30.628
Help me with the pillow, will you?

27:30.832 --> 27:33.960
Straighten it out.

27:34.169 --> 27:38.105
- Better?
- Yes.

27:38.440 --> 27:40.067
Did you sleep well?

27:40.275 --> 27:45.110
Sort of. How was your first day
as night guard?

27:45.414 --> 27:49.111
I took a whole pot of coffee.

27:50.519 --> 27:53.818
It's hard to be bound
to this bed.

27:54.756 --> 27:57.452
Think of something to do.

27:57.659 --> 27:59.422
With a broken leg?

28:00.295 --> 28:02.388
Didn't you use to stuff animals?

28:02.598 --> 28:05.431
That was ages ago,
I was just a girl.

28:05.634 --> 28:10.469
You made some money with
that taxi... taxi...

28:11.306 --> 28:13.297
Taxidermy.

28:14.109 --> 28:17.340
Go back to stuffing
and I'll try to sell it.

28:17.546 --> 28:18.740
All right.

28:20.582 --> 28:26.179
Before bed,
can you make me breakfast?

28:27.055 --> 28:30.752
With everything you deserve.

29:37.759 --> 29:39.693
Easy.

29:39.895 --> 29:44.662
- Hold on to me.
- Ok.

29:51.406 --> 29:53.465
- Happy?
- It's beautiful.

29:53.675 --> 29:56.667
Do you think I'll remember?

29:56.878 --> 30:01.713
- Learn again.
- Practicing, right?

30:05.187 --> 30:06.381
I'm going to bed.

30:06.588 --> 30:09.352
When you get up,
It'll be ready.

30:09.558 --> 30:12.391
- That quick?
- Yeah.

31:51.193 --> 31:53.058
Elvira.

32:26.528 --> 32:28.655
Hey! Over here.

32:30.198 --> 32:32.029
- It's me!
- Who?

32:32.234 --> 32:34.498
Me, Elvira.
The blender.

32:48.283 --> 32:52.811
If it's restless spirit, I'll have
a mass prayed for you, ok?

32:55.957 --> 32:57.925
That's senility, Elvira.

32:58.126 --> 32:59.115
Maybe it is.

32:59.327 --> 33:01.557
Or you're pulling my leg.

33:01.763 --> 33:02.752
Yeah, sure.

33:02.964 --> 33:04.727
Time to go.

33:04.933 --> 33:08.369
Careful or the blender
will catch you.

33:08.570 --> 33:10.663
Stop that.

33:20.548 --> 33:22.812
Elvira.

33:25.253 --> 33:27.653
Elvira.
Don't be frightened.

33:27.856 --> 33:30.791
It's me again.

33:30.992 --> 33:33.051
The blender.

33:34.162 --> 33:36.756
- You...?
- Yeah. It's me.

33:36.965 --> 33:41.698
I would love to talk.
Share some thoughts.

33:41.903 --> 33:45.634
I think I can... at least... try.
Do you want to?

33:46.775 --> 33:48.902
I'm going insane.

33:49.110 --> 33:53.513
- Or is this senility?
- What's senility?

33:56.017 --> 33:57.985
Senility is this.

33:58.720 --> 34:01.780
Me, talking to a machine.

34:01.990 --> 34:04.618
Chatting with a blender.

34:04.826 --> 34:06.726
I like that.

34:06.962 --> 34:09.260
Yeah. Senility.

34:09.464 --> 34:12.262
...that's right, Elvira.

34:13.401 --> 34:15.392
I like senility.

34:15.603 --> 34:17.070
Of course you like it.

34:17.272 --> 34:19.832
It's why you're
talking to me.

34:20.041 --> 34:23.533
And I listen. And answer!

34:23.745 --> 34:27.875
- Right?
- If you think so, then yes.

34:29.184 --> 34:33.280
Elvira, you have lovely teeth,
you know?

34:35.457 --> 34:38.392
- What?
- I like teeth.

34:38.593 --> 34:40.720
I like everything that cuts.

34:42.697 --> 34:45.530
I have good teeth too, don't I?

34:46.201 --> 34:49.659
- No, you've got blades.
... that cut.

34:49.871 --> 34:52.066
They really do.

34:53.375 --> 34:55.309
You look like a scorpion.

34:55.744 --> 34:58.304
What's a scorpion?

35:00.515 --> 35:05.612
It's an animal that stings
and poisons the blood.

35:05.820 --> 35:07.117
It kills the person.

35:07.322 --> 35:09.586
Kill? What's to kill?

35:12.327 --> 35:14.955
It's to send someone
six feet under.

35:15.163 --> 35:17.893
Six feet under what?

35:18.533 --> 35:21.900
What a funny expression.

35:22.203 --> 35:25.001
Cool. Six feet under.

35:25.206 --> 35:31.873
- Ms. Elvira. I'm coming in.
- Come in, honey.

35:34.883 --> 35:36.851
What's that, Ms. Elvira?

35:37.052 --> 35:39.612
- Never seen a stuffed animal before?
- No.

35:39.821 --> 35:41.755
Not up close.
it's weird.

35:41.956 --> 35:46.450
- Disgusting?
- Not disgusting. Just weird.

35:46.661 --> 35:48.925
I've done it since
I was a child.

35:49.130 --> 35:51.860
To each their own, right?

35:52.934 --> 35:55.266
I bet you're tired
of sitting there all day.

35:59.140 --> 36:02.109
A person's talking to me,
another comes...

36:02.310 --> 36:06.212
the person turns her back on me,
without even a goodnight.

36:06.748 --> 36:12.709
Old senile woman. How rude!

36:17.058 --> 36:20.152
- Is this ok, Ms. Elvira?
- Great.

36:20.395 --> 36:23.387
I'm lucky you have
strong arms to help me.

36:23.598 --> 36:26.294
Mary, mother of God.

36:26.734 --> 36:29.168
Don't mention
"arms" to me today.

36:29.370 --> 36:32.999
You remember my boss
at the store?

36:33.208 --> 36:35.108
Your boss?

36:35.510 --> 36:36.738
The one with the hairy arms?

36:36.945 --> 36:39.038
The very one.
Something happened...

36:39.247 --> 36:43.013
between us today
that was weird.

36:43.218 --> 36:44.651
He came to me with
a glass of water...

36:44.853 --> 36:47.822
his hairy arm sticking out,
just the way I like it.

36:48.022 --> 36:50.149
I went crazy, Ms. Elvira.

36:50.592 --> 36:52.822
- Did that go any further?
- No.

36:53.027 --> 36:56.326
No. It made me shiver,
that was all.

36:57.198 --> 37:00.599
Milena, stay away from that arm.

37:00.802 --> 37:03.270
Ms. Elvira, I swear to you
I want nothing with him.

37:03.471 --> 37:08.033
It was just that chill.
Nothing else.

37:10.845 --> 37:12.574
What?

37:13.047 --> 37:15.709
Come on, give me a break.

37:15.950 --> 37:17.713
Ah, Milena.

38:04.232 --> 38:07.963
Can I hold it?

38:09.404 --> 38:11.964
You're a real artist, Ms. Elvira.

38:12.173 --> 38:13.731
Later you can
remove the needles.

38:13.942 --> 38:18.072
And leave it to dry in the sun.

38:18.279 --> 38:19.610
My mother will love it.

38:19.814 --> 38:22.009
- This cat was your mother's?
- Yeah. Mauro.

38:22.217 --> 38:24.845
He died and I asked
her to stuff it.

38:25.119 --> 38:27.212
Mom won't believe it.

38:27.422 --> 38:29.822
Unbelievable,
stuffing mummy's kitten!

38:30.024 --> 38:31.855
Why don't you learn it?

38:32.060 --> 38:35.029
That's disgusting!

38:35.230 --> 38:36.754
Any money in it,
Ms. Elvira?

38:36.965 --> 38:39.695
Some change.
Rabbits sell well.

38:39.901 --> 38:41.163
Hello, folks.

38:41.369 --> 38:43.564
- What's up?
- Hello, Mr. Onofre.

38:43.771 --> 38:45.932
What's wrong, dear?

38:46.407 --> 38:49.171
- It's over.
- What do you mean?

38:49.510 --> 38:53.469
Some city officials took
away the animals.

38:53.748 --> 38:55.909
- The two ducks?
- Both. They said...

38:56.117 --> 39:00.110
it's illegal to sell animals
dead or alive.

39:01.289 --> 39:03.655
If they catch me again
I'll go to jail.

39:03.858 --> 39:06.452
The well has dried.

39:06.661 --> 39:10.757
I was just mentioning
I was making some change.

39:11.332 --> 39:13.926
No more stuffed animals.

39:28.082 --> 39:30.107
Why go to the movies?

39:30.318 --> 39:31.910
So you can have
a fit of jealousy?

39:32.120 --> 39:33.314
You were staring
at that bearded guy.

39:33.521 --> 39:35.182
Bearded who?

39:35.390 --> 39:37.620
Don't be coy.
The bearded fatso.

39:37.825 --> 39:41.124
- That hairy monkey?
- That's the one.

39:41.329 --> 39:43.092
You were drooling
all over him.

39:43.298 --> 39:45.766
Drooling?
Over that bushy face?

39:45.967 --> 39:48.595
You're a piece of work.

39:50.438 --> 39:53.566
Wellington, you know
I don't like hairy men.

39:54.742 --> 39:57.677
I'll tell you one thing.
If you cheat on me...

39:57.879 --> 39:59.608
I'll use a gun
the old fashioned way.

39:59.847 --> 40:03.112
Gun? You know
the kind of weapon I want?

40:03.318 --> 40:05.843
The magazine?
The ammunition?

40:06.054 --> 40:08.614
- Tell me, pumpkin pie.
- I'm driving.

40:08.823 --> 40:12.816
Pumpkin pie with a smooth,
smooth body.

40:13.027 --> 40:15.552
Open fire tonight, baby?

40:16.130 --> 40:17.688
Maybe a little open fire.

40:59.774 --> 41:02.334
- Good morning.
- Morning.

41:02.810 --> 41:06.371
- Remember me?
- Yes, sir.

41:08.783 --> 41:12.810
- I promised you a visit.
- Yes, sir. Come on in.

41:13.020 --> 41:16.456
- Anybody home?
- No, sir.

41:17.658 --> 41:20.627
Any sign of the husband?

41:21.829 --> 41:23.626
No, sir.

41:35.543 --> 41:38.068
He left everything here.

41:38.479 --> 41:41.915
You mean he vanished with
no belongings?

41:42.116 --> 41:44.141
Only what he was wearing.

41:44.552 --> 41:47.544
This is his work outfit.

41:49.857 --> 41:52.724
Tell me something.
Did he drink?

41:53.094 --> 41:56.257
Just a little beer
on Sundays.

41:56.464 --> 41:59.092
I see. But where?
And with whom?

41:59.300 --> 42:01.734
With his pals at the pub...

42:01.936 --> 42:07.135
or the next-door neighbor,
but he never got drunk.

42:07.341 --> 42:09.309
You may close it now.

42:11.145 --> 42:12.942
I'm doing a routine inspection.

42:13.147 --> 42:15.172
Don't touch any clothes.

42:15.383 --> 42:17.078
Leave everything as it is.

42:17.285 --> 42:18.775
Not even mine?

42:18.986 --> 42:21.079
Your clothes you may touch,
of course.

42:21.289 --> 42:23.655
But only yours.

42:23.858 --> 42:25.655
Not the victim's.

42:25.993 --> 42:28.860
- Victim?
- Your husband was murdered.

42:29.063 --> 42:32.123
Don't you take my hope away!

42:33.301 --> 42:34.928
What's that?

42:40.641 --> 42:42.131
Is anyone else here?

42:42.343 --> 42:44.334
It's just the blender.
It switches on by itself.

42:44.545 --> 42:47.070
- By itself?
- Wacked out machine.

42:47.281 --> 42:49.442
Don't turn it off.
Hold on.

42:52.186 --> 42:53.847
You mean he turns
on by itself?

42:54.055 --> 42:57.286
It kind of works
when it wants to.

42:57.492 --> 42:59.790
We used it
at the smoothie shop.

42:59.994 --> 43:01.393
What's in it?

43:01.596 --> 43:02.722
Beets.

43:02.930 --> 43:05.057
Blood-colored, eh?

43:05.266 --> 43:08.531
Beets are red, aren't they?
May I turn it off?

43:12.006 --> 43:14.600
There, old thing.
Calm down.

43:14.809 --> 43:16.606
Excuse me.

43:25.152 --> 43:27.211
Do you drink pure blood?

43:27.488 --> 43:29.080
What do you mean?

43:29.290 --> 43:32.782
Look... Doesn't it look like blood?

43:33.094 --> 43:35.324
Do I look like a vampire?

43:36.297 --> 43:39.164
You just like the
color of blood?

43:39.367 --> 43:41.597
Why do you talk
about blood so much?

43:41.802 --> 43:44.134
Why?
Does the word bother you?

43:45.740 --> 43:47.469
"Blood". You bothered?

43:47.675 --> 43:51.668
- Who isn't bothered by blood?
- Murderers.

43:52.046 --> 43:54.776
You certainly know
those better than I.

43:55.983 --> 44:00.283
Exactly. That's why they don't
escape me, get it?

44:00.488 --> 44:02.888
I can smell them.
Drink it.

44:03.090 --> 44:05.354
- What?
- A drink of blood. Drink it.

44:05.560 --> 44:07.858
Leave my beets alone, sir.

44:08.062 --> 44:09.962
Drink up a little blood, ma'am.

44:10.164 --> 44:12.394
When you came in
I was making soup.

44:12.600 --> 44:16.161
May I carry on in peace,
please, Detective?

44:16.370 --> 44:18.895
Drink up half a glass of this...

44:19.106 --> 44:22.542
red liquid, better?

44:22.743 --> 44:28.306
I recognize a murderer's face when
they intake the color of blood.

44:34.755 --> 44:36.950
There.
Any blood on my face?

44:37.592 --> 44:40.459
No, but you drank too quickly.
Straight down the throat.

44:40.661 --> 44:43.653
Drink it slowly.
Gulp by gulp. Slowly.

44:43.864 --> 44:46.355
Leave the blood
on your tongue a while.

44:57.278 --> 44:59.576
Beets are sweet as blood,
aren't they?

44:59.780 --> 45:02.340
It needs a pinch of salt.

45:02.550 --> 45:05.075
I hadn't seasoned the broth.

45:29.210 --> 45:32.702
- Moist soil, Ms. Elvira.
- It's my garden, sir.

45:32.913 --> 45:36.144
- It's been recently watered.
- I water it every day.

45:36.350 --> 45:39.046
I will have it dug
six feet under.

45:40.287 --> 45:42.915
And who will pay for
the damage?

45:43.124 --> 45:45.456
I've seen cases like this,
Ms. Elvira.

45:45.660 --> 45:48.220
The victim buried
in his own backyard.

45:48.429 --> 45:50.226
I'll send the bill
to the Lieutenant.

45:50.431 --> 45:53.195
One buck for each
ruined vegetable.

45:54.769 --> 45:56.532
The police has
full authority.

45:56.737 --> 46:00.798
To investigate, not to
wreck private property.

46:01.008 --> 46:05.240
Who knows how badly
the victim was wrecked!

46:06.580 --> 46:09.913
You get shivers
every time I say "victim".

46:10.117 --> 46:12.312
I do?

46:13.320 --> 46:17.848
You get speechless,
dead silent.

46:18.059 --> 46:20.220
It's because this suspicion...

46:20.428 --> 46:22.396
Go on?

46:22.730 --> 46:25.324
If only you knew
what I want to say.

46:25.533 --> 46:28.263
Just get it off your chest,
Ms. Elvira.

46:29.103 --> 46:32.732
You can stick this suspicion
where the sun doesn't shine!

46:38.879 --> 46:41.473
You can't arrest me
without evidence.

46:41.682 --> 46:44.344
We each have our own
delights, ma'am.

46:44.552 --> 46:46.019
This is mine.

46:46.220 --> 46:47.585
Cuffing away the suspect.

46:47.788 --> 46:51.155
You know why?
If you slay, I'll make you pay.

46:51.358 --> 46:52.882
Keep that in mind!

46:53.094 --> 46:56.222
If you slay, I'll make you pay.

47:00.534 --> 47:02.058
Fuinha is a madcap.

47:02.269 --> 47:04.669
Everyone has their own method.
This is mine.

47:04.905 --> 47:07.396
Take it easy, Fuinha.

47:07.608 --> 47:09.439
I'm taking it easy, sir.

47:09.643 --> 47:11.577
I catch the smell
of blood, get it?

47:11.779 --> 47:13.610
It's my sixth sense.

47:13.814 --> 47:17.113
A murderers' sweat changes.

47:17.318 --> 47:19.786
The more they try to hide it...

47:19.987 --> 47:22.649
the more I sense the blood.

47:23.257 --> 47:26.192
This old lady spilled
her husband's blood.

47:26.560 --> 47:29.688
The stench is coming
out through her pores.

47:29.897 --> 47:31.660
You said the same
about that other lady.

47:31.866 --> 47:35.165
The doctor's widow.
Stench, pores...

47:35.369 --> 47:36.768
talk about a slip-up!

47:36.971 --> 47:40.532
Only God is infallible, pal.
And not always.

47:40.741 --> 47:44.199
That's why I tell you.
Slow down, Fuinha.

47:44.411 --> 47:46.902
Easy on the shock treatment.

47:47.414 --> 47:50.349
No sweat, boss.
You can count on me.

47:50.551 --> 47:53.145
I'll find the corpse.

47:59.093 --> 48:01.254
Wellington can get
you a lawyer, Ms. Elvira.

48:01.462 --> 48:02.929
What's this cop thinking?

48:03.130 --> 48:05.997
That he can wave handcuffs
in your face like that?

48:06.300 --> 48:08.928
He gave me the creeps.
I almost had a fit.

48:09.136 --> 48:12.196
Relax, Ms. Elvira,
have some tea.

48:12.406 --> 48:13.395
I have to go.

48:13.607 --> 48:17.941
- Godspeed.
- Same to you.

48:26.654 --> 48:28.781
What did that busybody want?

48:32.092 --> 48:36.461
Why did you have to
turn on right then?

48:36.664 --> 48:39.394
I got nervous.
Couldn't help it.

48:39.600 --> 48:42.262
You almost ruined everything.

48:42.469 --> 48:45.199
What about you and your beets?

48:45.406 --> 48:48.341
It was the only thing
in the fridge.

48:50.444 --> 48:54.107
Justice be done.
You tap danced around him.

48:54.615 --> 48:56.207
You think?

48:56.417 --> 48:59.545
It's fair to say you tap
danced around him...

48:59.753 --> 49:01.277
and committed
the perfect crime.

49:01.488 --> 49:05.618
Both of us did.
You were a great accomplice.

49:05.826 --> 49:07.953
Thank you.

49:08.996 --> 49:11.487
As a matter of fact,
I was always an accomplice.

49:11.699 --> 49:13.997
Even back at the
smoothie shop.

49:14.201 --> 49:17.602
Actually, I don't know
if I was accomplice or a victim.

49:25.512 --> 49:29.312
What I do know is that people
say things meaning one thing...

49:29.516 --> 49:32.349
But their attitudes
mean the opposite.

49:32.553 --> 49:34.783
When they're interested,
they're full of pretty words...

49:34.989 --> 49:37.787
But when they are contested,
there comes ingratitude.

49:37.992 --> 49:39.357
There comes poison.

49:41.428 --> 49:43.225
You going out?

49:43.931 --> 49:47.389
Overtime, Elvira.
Overtime.

49:47.601 --> 49:51.093
Overtime.
There's no time for us anymore.

49:52.539 --> 49:54.871
No more Saturday,
no more Sunday...

49:55.075 --> 49:57.635
and now no more
Monday either.

49:57.845 --> 50:00.609
Too much work is
better than no work.

50:01.382 --> 50:04.044
I bought some
chicken for lunch.

50:04.251 --> 50:06.549
But you'll eat at work, right?

50:14.228 --> 50:15.889
Good news.

50:16.096 --> 50:19.429
I found a buyer
for blabbermouth.

50:20.467 --> 50:23.493
The owner of the bar by my job.

50:23.704 --> 50:25.831
I told him I fixed it...

50:26.040 --> 50:27.837
and he wants to see it.

50:28.042 --> 50:30.909
- Don't sell it, please.
- How come?

50:31.111 --> 50:32.908
At home it's still
good for something.

50:33.113 --> 50:37.243
That's precisely why we haven't
bought a new one.

50:37.618 --> 50:40.178
He's growing on me.

50:56.603 --> 51:00.198
- I'm going.
- Take care.

51:11.952 --> 51:14.921
That hurt me deeply.

51:15.122 --> 51:17.682
I left with a complete
sense of abandonment.

51:18.325 --> 51:20.725
A true piece of junk.

51:27.267 --> 51:29.633
But one thing is now clear to me...

51:29.837 --> 51:33.204
human feelings are like
a double-edged blade...

51:33.841 --> 51:39.780
one knife smoothes your vanity
the other cuts into your pride.

51:57.698 --> 52:00.258
Back with the blabbermouth?

52:00.467 --> 52:02.958
I thought you'd bring a new blender.

52:03.270 --> 52:06.239
When I get my pay,
I'll buy a new one.

52:07.274 --> 52:09.834
And why the triple shift?

52:10.044 --> 52:13.036
Something wrong
with the other guards.

52:14.014 --> 52:16.642
There's a swap this week.

52:17.284 --> 52:21.015
Where did you get that tan?

52:21.522 --> 52:23.820
Day shifts are sunny...

52:24.324 --> 52:26.656
the night doesn't
give you a tan.

52:26.860 --> 52:28.020
I'm very tired.

52:28.228 --> 52:31.459
I made you some cabbage soup.

52:31.665 --> 52:36.034
I had a snack at the factory.
I'm tired, not hungry.

52:36.236 --> 52:39.933
I'll take a shower
and go straight to bed.

52:40.140 --> 52:42.973
This shift change throws me off.

52:43.177 --> 52:47.079
Can't rely on the clock,
it's crazy...

52:55.189 --> 52:57.851
Didn't even bother
getting me out.

52:58.058 --> 53:02.085
She laid anguished in bed.

53:03.764 --> 53:08.724
Well deserved,
I must say.

53:11.071 --> 53:14.234
So they didn't want
you at the bar?

53:14.441 --> 53:17.535
You piece of junk.
Doesn't matter.

53:17.744 --> 53:20.770
You're still useful here.

53:22.850 --> 53:27.310
Not even with your iron tongue
did they want you.

53:27.521 --> 53:31.184
That's aging for you.
Old Thing.

53:34.928 --> 53:37.761
What kind of test
did they put you through?

53:37.965 --> 53:40.365
Sand and oil.

53:41.668 --> 53:46.230
What did they think you were?
A construction tool?

53:48.142 --> 53:52.169
You poor thing.

53:57.518 --> 54:00.282
Why are you quiet
like a rock?

54:00.487 --> 54:05.424
Have you lost your ability
to talk, to understand?

54:07.995 --> 54:10.293
Jammed for good.

54:12.766 --> 54:14.631
I saw the ocean.

54:15.068 --> 54:18.868
- At last you're talking.
- Yeah. I saw the waves.

54:19.072 --> 54:22.974
- What?
- I didn't like it at all.

54:23.210 --> 54:24.643
Where did you see the ocean?

54:24.845 --> 54:29.339
Too much water. Too noisy.
I prefer the fountain.

54:29.550 --> 54:30.744
What's this about the ocean?

54:30.951 --> 54:34.318
You've never seen the sea?

54:34.521 --> 54:37.388
What's this about?
Never been where?

54:37.591 --> 54:39.491
Guarujá.

54:39.726 --> 54:42.354
Who took you to Guarujá?
The bar owner?

54:42.563 --> 54:46.226
Bar? What bar?
I don't belong in bars.

54:46.433 --> 54:49.459
What the hell in this?

54:49.836 --> 54:51.929
Working, it must sound
like a jackhammer.

54:52.139 --> 54:55.267
Gimme banana and milk.

54:55.475 --> 55:02.142
Looks like a Russian submarine.

55:02.482 --> 55:06.316
You'll pay by the dose, guys.

55:07.521 --> 55:08.852
A dose each.

55:09.389 --> 55:14.349
Here goes nothing.

55:14.561 --> 55:16.324
What the hell?

55:16.530 --> 55:17.929
Is this outlet working?

55:18.131 --> 55:22.090
Of course it is,
the TV was here.

55:23.870 --> 55:25.838
How did you
end up at the beach?

55:26.039 --> 55:28.837
Onofre threw me in the
backseat of the car.

55:29.042 --> 55:30.339
What car?

55:30.877 --> 55:34.244
The car that took us
to Guarujá, of course.

55:34.448 --> 55:36.507
- Whose car?
- The lady's.

55:36.717 --> 55:37.945
What lady?

55:38.151 --> 55:40.745
Spit it out. What lady? What car?

55:40.954 --> 55:43.684
- If you want to know, go there.
- Go where?

55:43.890 --> 55:46.620
To Santos.
They went there today.

55:46.827 --> 55:50.661
Listen, Onofre left for work...

55:50.897 --> 55:52.057
Yesterday Guarujá.
Today, Santos.

55:52.266 --> 55:55.201
Tomorrow, Peruíbe,
then, Praia Grande.

55:55.402 --> 55:56.391
Four days at the beach.

55:56.603 --> 55:59.071
When parting, she said,
"beach tomorrow, honey?"

55:59.273 --> 56:01.969
And he replied,
"beach tomorrow, doll. "

56:02.843 --> 56:06.574
- He isn't in today?
- He'll be out 'til Thursday.

56:06.780 --> 56:09.078
- Who's this?
- A friend of the family's.

56:09.283 --> 56:11.274
- Do you have his house number?
- Yes.

56:11.485 --> 56:15.012
I've tried, nobody answers.
I'll try again. Thank you.

56:15.555 --> 56:20.754
This is not happening.
It's a nightmare.

56:24.464 --> 56:28.161
I'm dreaming.
This isn't real.

56:28.368 --> 56:32.634
It can't be.
It can't be true!

56:32.973 --> 56:39.208
There was no beach, no car,
no Guarujá, no honey, no doll.

56:40.180 --> 56:42.444
Someone will have
to prove it.

56:42.649 --> 56:45.948
I need proof...
I need proof!

56:47.154 --> 56:49.213
Where's the evidence
that you exist?

56:49.423 --> 56:53.985
That you talk, feel...
React like a person?

58:27.087 --> 58:29.146
It's him.

01:02:15.615 --> 01:02:19.210
So, those were the so-called guts.
Piece of cake.

01:02:19.419 --> 01:02:21.853
Piece of cake, of course.
Heart, stomach, bowels.

01:02:22.055 --> 01:02:25.752
Let's see some bones!
Bones are the tough part.

01:02:25.959 --> 01:02:27.517
What's the matter with bones?

01:02:27.727 --> 01:02:29.388
You'll see.

01:02:30.296 --> 01:02:31.593
What's the ice for?

01:02:31.798 --> 01:02:33.390
You don't like it?

01:02:33.633 --> 01:02:34.930
They're ok.

01:02:35.135 --> 01:02:39.196
- Then stop complaining.
- I'm not complaining, Elvira.

01:02:39.406 --> 01:02:42.068
I'm only trying
to understand.

01:02:42.275 --> 01:02:45.403
Ice and bones are a good match.

01:02:46.046 --> 01:02:49.379
Both are white and hard.

01:02:51.151 --> 01:02:54.746
- I still don't get it.
- You'll get it now.

01:02:54.954 --> 01:02:56.512
Grind.

01:04:11.998 --> 01:04:14.933
Premium eggs on sale.

01:04:15.135 --> 01:04:18.571
Potatoes. Onions. Garlic.

01:04:18.772 --> 01:04:23.732
Oranges. Lime.
Quayle eggs.

01:04:24.043 --> 01:04:28.503
Bananas. Tomatoes.
Sweet Potatoes.

01:04:49.602 --> 01:04:51.263
Yes?

01:04:52.806 --> 01:04:58.244
Are you aware of any quibbles
between them recently?

01:04:58.878 --> 01:05:01.574
- Was he rude, for example?
- No.

01:05:01.781 --> 01:05:04.978
Quite the opposite.
He treated her like a queen.

01:05:06.019 --> 01:05:11.321
I've also heard old Onofre
was a bit of a lady's man.

01:05:13.359 --> 01:05:16.954
- Did he ever come on to you?
- Never! No way.

01:05:17.964 --> 01:05:20.592
He was never fresh with me.

01:05:20.800 --> 01:05:24.065
You never caught
him looking...

01:05:24.270 --> 01:05:26.431
at your...

01:05:26.639 --> 01:05:28.971
or at your...?

01:05:29.175 --> 01:05:32.144
My what, sir?

01:05:32.345 --> 01:05:34.506
No offense, ma'am.
I'm investigating!

01:05:34.714 --> 01:05:37.376
I meant your legs,
your knees, get it?

01:05:37.951 --> 01:05:41.785
He peeped at my legs
with eyes like this.

01:05:42.055 --> 01:05:43.215
You don't say!

01:05:43.423 --> 01:05:46.722
He asked me
"what do you think of oral sex?"

01:05:46.926 --> 01:05:51.090
Christ! This man must be denounced!
That's harassment.

01:05:51.297 --> 01:05:55.097
I replied, "sex to me is a relationship
of complete freedom".

01:05:55.301 --> 01:05:57.326
If the partner wants and deserves it,
he takes what he gives.

01:05:57.537 --> 01:06:00.631
He opened his little eye
at me, like that...

01:06:00.840 --> 01:06:03.934
got up, put his hand in his pocket.

01:06:04.444 --> 01:06:06.878
He was totally aroused!

01:06:07.113 --> 01:06:09.308
I thought he'd grab
me right there...

01:06:09.515 --> 01:06:12.416
and spread my legs.
That thin little nose...

01:06:12.619 --> 01:06:15.588
like a penis stuck to his face.

01:06:18.391 --> 01:06:19.790
How long have you
known them?

01:06:19.993 --> 01:06:23.451
About five years. Since I
started delivering mail there.

01:06:24.297 --> 01:06:26.356
I heard you're
close to Elvira.

01:06:26.566 --> 01:06:29.194
I also heard sometimes
you suck on her shakes.

01:06:29.435 --> 01:06:32.336
Yeah. Sometimes
she's kind enough to offer.

01:06:32.538 --> 01:06:36.497
She only gives you that sort
of shake or other types too?

01:06:36.709 --> 01:06:40.167
Come on. Ms. Elvira is a lady.
I call her auntie.

01:06:40.613 --> 01:06:44.242
Funny. I know a fellow who
called his neighbor "granny"...

01:06:44.450 --> 01:06:46.384
and she sat on his face.

01:06:47.320 --> 01:06:48.378
Tell me...

01:06:48.588 --> 01:06:51.352
Onofre was kind of naughty,
wasn't he?

01:06:51.557 --> 01:06:53.081
Tell me the truth.

01:06:53.293 --> 01:06:55.352
No. We only talked soccer.

01:06:55.561 --> 01:06:58.689
But I did see him
at the hospital once.

01:07:01.234 --> 01:07:03.702
I was around and I saw it.
It was really him.

01:07:03.903 --> 01:07:06.064
He was with a lady.
Excited, see?

01:07:06.272 --> 01:07:08.206
- So was she.
- I'm understanding...

01:07:08.541 --> 01:07:12.238
I recently told Ms. Elvira.

01:07:12.445 --> 01:07:17.280
I knew there was something
fishy here.

01:07:17.483 --> 01:07:21.044
That's it.
I had four days off...

01:07:21.254 --> 01:07:22.812
because I had
doubled my shift.

01:07:23.022 --> 01:07:24.990
He did the same
thing at his job.

01:07:25.191 --> 01:07:27.318
So, you arranged that?

01:07:27.894 --> 01:07:30.954
Yes, so we could have
a small honeymoon.

01:07:31.164 --> 01:07:33.359
You know what I mean.

01:07:33.566 --> 01:07:35.261
How did you meet him?

01:07:35.468 --> 01:07:40.633
His company sent him to the
hospital where I work as a nurse.

01:07:42.475 --> 01:07:45.035
Twelve by eight.
Your blood pressure's fine.

01:07:45.244 --> 01:07:47.178
That's nice.

01:07:47.413 --> 01:07:51.372
- Let's check your heart now.
- Yes, let's.

01:07:51.918 --> 01:07:56.480
Inhale. Exhale. Inhale.

01:07:58.324 --> 01:08:02.784
Inhale again.
Exhale slowly.

01:08:02.996 --> 01:08:05.897
That's it. Again.

01:08:06.132 --> 01:08:08.623
Inhale.

01:08:09.135 --> 01:08:13.401
Exhale.
That's it.

01:08:15.074 --> 01:08:18.532
I think my pressure's rising!

01:08:22.348 --> 01:08:24.714
So, the old man whiffed
you right in.

01:08:26.986 --> 01:08:30.854
I am very sensitive
in that area.

01:08:31.124 --> 01:08:34.457
But it was only physical
in the beginning.

01:08:34.660 --> 01:08:36.787
Later a great love ensued.

01:08:37.096 --> 01:08:40.031
He was gonna leave
his wife for me.

01:08:40.233 --> 01:08:43.134
I'm sure he wouldn't
vanish like this.

01:08:44.070 --> 01:08:45.867
Someone got rid of him.

01:08:46.072 --> 01:08:49.041
Either his wife or a hired gun.

01:09:28.614 --> 01:09:31.447
I played you for a sucker?

01:09:33.352 --> 01:09:36.651
Why didn't you tell me
straight away about the nurse?

01:09:38.825 --> 01:09:40.486
Because when
the mailman came by...

01:09:40.693 --> 01:09:43.025
I had already been to the station.

01:09:43.229 --> 01:09:45.993
Then why not tell me right after?

01:09:46.332 --> 01:09:48.630
Because I don't believe it.

01:09:48.835 --> 01:09:52.271
That mailman has a big mouth.
Loves to gossip.

01:09:55.675 --> 01:09:58.906
I heard that you...

01:09:59.112 --> 01:10:01.103
stuff animals.

01:10:01.681 --> 01:10:04.013
Yes, sir.

01:10:04.984 --> 01:10:10.217
What weapons do you
use to embalm them?

01:10:10.623 --> 01:10:13.285
They're instruments
not weapons.

01:10:13.493 --> 01:10:15.791
My father was
in the business.

01:10:15.995 --> 01:10:20.591
He made this one.
I learned as a little girl.

01:10:23.503 --> 01:10:26.165
Tell me something,
Ms. Elvira...

01:10:26.372 --> 01:10:30.866
how long did it take you
to embalm your husband?

01:10:32.044 --> 01:10:33.568
Please, Detective.

01:10:33.779 --> 01:10:34.939
One week?

01:10:37.049 --> 01:10:38.710
42 years.

01:10:39.218 --> 01:10:43.154
I spent the entire marriage
embalming my husband.

01:10:44.524 --> 01:10:46.014
I'm telling you.

01:10:46.225 --> 01:10:48.659
Piercing objects
laying around.

01:10:48.861 --> 01:10:51.591
Needles, scissors,
a hoe, a hatchet.

01:10:51.797 --> 01:10:53.526
A load of weapons, sir.

01:10:53.733 --> 01:10:56.065
So, which one did
she use, Fuinha?

01:10:56.269 --> 01:10:58.499
Beats me.

01:10:58.704 --> 01:11:01.172
The first blow may
have been with the hoe.

01:11:01.374 --> 01:11:03.569
The victim in the backyard.

01:11:03.843 --> 01:11:06.539
The old man squatting,
gardening.

01:11:06.746 --> 01:11:09.214
She comes from behind and
hits him with the hoe.

01:11:09.415 --> 01:11:11.383
Get it, Chief?

01:11:11.584 --> 01:11:13.142
But don't they
have neighbors?

01:11:13.352 --> 01:11:15.343
Sure. A married couple.

01:11:15.555 --> 01:11:18.388
By the way, there's
a second theory.

01:11:18.858 --> 01:11:21.452
Maybe it wasn't in the yard...

01:11:21.661 --> 01:11:23.629
but in the kitchen.

01:11:23.829 --> 01:11:25.797
He's there, waiting for supper...

01:11:25.998 --> 01:11:29.297
she comes back with
a knife instead a soup.

01:11:29.502 --> 01:11:32.960
And then, she chops his
head off. Maybe.

01:11:33.172 --> 01:11:36.608
One blow, two three.

01:11:39.445 --> 01:11:42.209
But there's also a third theory.

01:11:43.349 --> 01:11:45.681
He's asleep...

01:11:45.885 --> 01:11:48.615
she grabs her
embalming needles...

01:11:48.821 --> 01:11:52.518
tiptoes into
the silent room and...

01:11:52.758 --> 01:11:56.421
sticks the needles into
the victim's ears, Chief.

01:11:58.030 --> 01:12:00.726
Then, the hatchet.

01:12:01.801 --> 01:12:04.497
Then the blender.

01:12:07.873 --> 01:12:09.841
She made minced meat
out of her husband...

01:12:10.042 --> 01:12:11.600
and got rid of
the body in the blender.

01:12:11.811 --> 01:12:14.279
Piece by piece.
Bone by bone.

01:12:14.480 --> 01:12:17.005
Is that your conclusion, Fuinha?

01:12:18.050 --> 01:12:19.483
Bull's eye, Chief.

01:12:19.685 --> 01:12:21.448
Grinding bone in a blender.

01:12:21.654 --> 01:12:23.281
Gimme a break.

01:12:23.489 --> 01:12:27.653
We're overwhelmed with work...

01:12:27.860 --> 01:12:31.819
and you come to me
with this fabrication!

01:13:40.433 --> 01:13:41.525
Come in.

01:13:41.734 --> 01:13:44.635
I need your honest opinion.

01:13:44.837 --> 01:13:46.771
What is it, Milena?

01:13:48.040 --> 01:13:51.874
It's nothing serious.
But it's important to me.

01:13:52.278 --> 01:13:54.678
Did you know
that celebrities...

01:13:54.880 --> 01:13:58.680
not all, but many...
aren't wearing them anymore.

01:13:58.884 --> 01:14:00.818
Not wearing what?

01:14:01.020 --> 01:14:03.614
- Panties.
- Working with no panties on?

01:14:03.823 --> 01:14:07.520
Not to outline the fabric,
you see?

01:14:08.494 --> 01:14:10.792
- I don't believe it.
- Oh yes.

01:14:10.996 --> 01:14:13.624
- Come on.
- Look now.

01:14:13.833 --> 01:14:15.596
Milena!

01:14:16.135 --> 01:14:19.104
- Stop it, girl.
- Bye, Ms. Elvira.

01:14:19.939 --> 01:14:22.464
I should remember more
about the human body.

01:14:23.042 --> 01:14:26.239
Each part is the enemy
of the other parts.

01:14:26.946 --> 01:14:28.971
The ears twist
what they hear...

01:14:29.181 --> 01:14:31.649
the eyes distort
what they see...

01:14:31.851 --> 01:14:35.582
the tongue uses
phrases to seduce...

01:14:35.788 --> 01:14:38.780
to befuddle, to better
or worsen things...

01:14:38.991 --> 01:14:41.221
according to its mood.

01:14:43.362 --> 01:14:49.198
I have no ears, eyes or mouth,
but it's as if I did.

01:14:49.702 --> 01:14:53.160
I got this trait from
living with people...

01:14:54.373 --> 01:14:57.308
People who gave me
an awareness of life...

01:14:57.510 --> 01:15:01.207
but also an awareness
of death.

01:15:01.414 --> 01:15:05.077
Now I know what it means
to be "six feet under".

01:15:11.891 --> 01:15:14.883
But in spite of all,
if I could choose...

01:15:15.094 --> 01:15:18.257
if I could go back to being
a simple kitchen appliance...

01:15:18.464 --> 01:15:22.833
insensitive and mute,
I don't know if I'd want to.

01:15:25.271 --> 01:15:28.172
Hmm, no, I wouldn't.

01:15:28.574 --> 01:15:32.510
To think is addictive,
to feel is like booze...

01:15:32.711 --> 01:15:36.477
and all this restless waiting,
filled with passion and fear...

01:15:36.682 --> 01:15:39.082
it all that fascinates me.

01:15:39.885 --> 01:15:44.822
What fate has in store for me
is a mystery, a threat...

01:15:46.625 --> 01:15:48.354
but until then...

01:15:48.561 --> 01:15:51.189
as the night presses on...

01:15:51.397 --> 01:15:55.265
my screws will sing
their way into the night!

01:15:59.338 --> 01:16:01.465
Sing, my little bird!

01:16:01.674 --> 01:16:05.770
Sing old gadget, offspring
of both God and...

01:16:05.978 --> 01:16:10.438
Satan!
Sing, glorious blender!
